Statement

Rewrite the guardian code in the above example without
two if statements. Instead, use a compound logical expression using
the or logical operator with a single if statement


Solution

f=open("C:\code\Romeo.txt","r")
list_of_unique_words=[]
list_of_words=[]
for lines in f:
    words=lines.split()
    for word in words:
        if word not in list_of_unique_words[0:]:
          list_of_unique_words.append(word)
        else:
          list_of_words.append(word)
list_of_unique_words.sort()
list_of_words.sort()
print(list_of_unique_words)
print(list_of_words)
